[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating timestamp formatting**\n\nI'm thinking about hardcoding names and whether they can be version-agnostic. While names are public and generally stable, it feels a bit brittle to me. I want to avoid having to retest the class altogether. I see that the existing Slf4jLogger is configured but doesn't directly format the timestamp. My next step might be to introduce a new test that checks if the timestamp formatting adheres to ISO UTC for epoch time.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_052afa5fa4bb68260169fb537242d081a0a53142ec1f02f203\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-1N8Dy9nH2dE-NMiQHC8coKUPZqiH5AAtiOj_FjqFc3jPxwXV6N5nFLQkr_dxAZo1vs-fS5xGn4wHpBVXzD93BEttIy6H_mhl9dOoUWcO3qosJdmWgricpSSS68V5XT-2r1qC0MyadFoPoC539rPbe59CUMPCu1zPe1u76-EiZfQZqjqhbSBBQyyo5mfoL9KcRkw-ITGsKVfVUL_nhp5srNbvwNR0JMgG1fwsap9lE3qNM3yYAn7dCg2nvOJ-l_v72eCGQRjw2d6CNi0RqdfJXYbYi7oaK-Povl-cbpZGL2KvOLF47DNwAq5k8U4ZAoEK1Gj7Z_LXw1yNBOD0j-FI5nW0a9tTVwGBCHrNhiaokGZa8YTZ1IIYBGunGOHZtqTPyPT7hg_oRb7MRwo9THcOxjeDTvS8YtLCzaHyKUrOpsmKbW3tCaM9Jd1m3s5jyXMN8jmuMjvUudphrT2I16P-7AOO1gFHtq6cYRN-LLFRqYcFhjPP3IWkmEsYgNX_GDqNiCbpDYxYQ2Y-fTcQou_WxQ_sGvf8D3isxnwuh7GuB8yMdeodvWo8Zt52oOKClBnbmWL79gKIez9UvPJV6QWwLwd-fP0A7OWTaRcrSIQTr4tLgyRPzolr-3UQwpj0g4EEeypSsNQl3vztKLj7c6jqoJn5U2m2VvNyxMnmehv1jfjuBQJof8Ovh1w8YEgLEWBn1l6GKgZVimByiodJ0DdGP2bg5Aysz6xu7bbrH3YhDlzct5LVMFzlpcCKNLddN6RWIfIdcxWBDtvDDBnDQK_Td1IfJ1QQKEozkevl1dE6rEEYgglwLU7OXSqKJN8MmrgMfrM3aUFV3TFh2kc7c_hdns0ZUKnUOWPJrf4_cJIdjhExqO-RGk7aSUN385ilzWuutwwlgpCTRuXpsUV4-2g-eOP1YNYRWHsAxyD5Xq4dx6waF4Pe09Hve6Pi1wdaGgeYdvu9yilqewd0L0KBn3c9YFisE_cxTXp6ZgPgfA6mMLq1IscndlJLIv4Iaqaa7WlE3X6TFPmwvbkJ5rh8sPIToZ3KwDl8zhG3nvvwlRuz5CyN0VZySkRQ2XvRsrRhCK3r3uulfxFX7kTpzI28Xfb9i8oAwQOVUzvdOSradkB-bHKk9QU9elUsxlaYljgM5ZUPMSuL8t8IIFGXlQIQ7dwUzc3Il44-U5GfDm3g1xkDlpAZijDdQeDu0RoKVtIRASOQlDE823Vjp1YiwQlymyS2YSy0_4dVv4SRfeE_cvXVXG80GQmlv2UeOHswF9AcSgcZo6rx2X